Subject: [PATCH] orangepi4pro: disable unpopulated AC101 audio machine

The board uses the ES8388 codec on the 3.5mm jack (i2s4) and HDMI audio (i2s3),
both of which register fine (ALSA cards sndi2s4 / allwinner-hdmi). The DT also
leaves the AC101 sound machine (i2s0_mach) enabled, but i2s0_plat is disabled and
the board has no AC101 codec, so its DAI link fails to resolve and the ASoC
simple-card core logs "simple_dai_link_of failed" repeatedly (deferred-probe
retries). Disable the AC101 machine to silence the noise. No functional change:
working audio is on i2s4 (ES8388) and i2s3 (HDMI).

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts
index 4468cc2e6..3dddacb3a 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts
@@ -2791,7 +2791,7 @@ &i2s0_mach {
                   "SPK", "LINEOUTRN_PIN",
                   "HPOUTL", "HPOUTL_PIN",
                   "HPOUTR", "HPOUTR_PIN";
-    status        = "okay";
+    status        = "disabled"; /* OPi4Pro: AC101 codec not populated (board uses ES8388 on i2s4); i2s0_plat disabled -> silences simple_dai_link_of failed */
     i2s0_cpu: soundcard-mach,cpu {
         sound-dai = <&i2s0_plat>;
         /* note: pll freq = 24.576M or 22.5792M * pll-fs */
